trend_summary: Built-up land slowly expanded along the northern riverfront, with new roads and scattered subdivisions pushing southward. Forest cover declined in several interior patches, converted mainly to pasture or cropland. A few isolated clearings appeared in the east, while water margins shifted slightly. Overall change is gradual, keeping the peninsula largely green and low-density.
notable_changes: Incremental spread of housing and streets along the northern shoreline settlement core.
Several forest blocks in the central and southern interior cleared for fields or pasture.
Emergence of a large light-toned clearing in the eastern sector, likely a quarry or utility site.
River and tidal-flat morphology altered, with broader muddy bars visible in later images.
Progressive infill of small lots between existing houses, indicating slow suburbanisation.
